<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Iddings</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-21"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 50.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 81, of August 29
                            last, I have to say that the Department will be pleased to have you send
                            to it three copies of the recent Italian convention with the Sultan of
                            Somaliland as soon as it shall have been published by the Italian
                            Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>